get the correct structure in place for the deployment.\n\n\n**Adjusting and Deploying**\n\nNow, I'm working to integrate the corrected `render.yaml` with the existing setup, and I'm generating a deployment script. I'll include concise, step-by-step instructions for using the updated `render.yaml` file on Render. My aim is to make the next steps seamless.\n\n\n**Generating Deployment Script**\n\nI'm now integrating the corrections and will provide a straightforward script. I'll outline the steps for deploying this `render.yaml` file, ensuring the user can easily deploy their application on Render after that page refresh. I'm focusing on simplicity and ease of use.\n\n\n**Creating the Correct Diff**\n\nNow I'm crafting the final diff to correct the `render.yaml` file, ready to share with the user. I'll make sure the `databases` definitions are placed correctly at the top level, based on Render's specifications, removing the incorrect `psql` type declaration under `services`.\n\n\n**Preparing the Response**\n\nNow I'm finalizing the response, ensuring that the corrected `render.yaml` diff and deployment instructions are clear and easy to follow. I want to convey that using the Blueprint setup means they won't lose their configurations again.\n\n\n**Summarizing and Finalizing**\n\nI'm now integrating the corrections and putting together the diff and instructions, preparing the complete response. I've double-checked the steps to deploy the application with the corrected `render.yaml` file, ensuring it's easy to follow. I'm focusing on providing the user a seamless process for their deployment.\n\n\n**Summarizing the Solution**\n\nI'm now putting together the corrected `render.yaml` diff and deployment instructions, along with some added context. The goal is to make it super easy for the user to deploy their application, even after the page refresh. It should be a much smoother experience.\n\n\n","id":"32c14d5b-a1fd-461c-89d0-71c92f3eac88","agentMetadata":{"coderAgent":{"kind":""},"model":""},"modelDisplayName":"3.1 Pro Preview","modelID":"chat-gemini-3-1-pro-preview-paid-tier"},{"entity":"USER","markdownText":"How can I securely pass my JWT_SECRET to Render using the render.yaml file?","chatSectionId":"1","ideContext":{"currentFile":{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/render.yaml","language":"yaml","selection":{"start":828,"end":828},"includedReason":"CURRENTLY_OPEN"},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":[{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","language":"dockerfile","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CHAT_FILE_REFERENCED"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/cors/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/@types/node/diagnostics_channel.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/@types/node/diagnostics_channel.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/@aws-sdk/client-s3/dist-types/commands/PutBucketTaggingCommand.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/@aws-sdk/client-s3/dist-types/commands/PutBucketTaggingCommand.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/@types/node/timers.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/@types/node/timers.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/csstype/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/delayed-stream/Readme.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/@aws-sdk/nested-clients/dist-types/submodules/sso/index.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"}],"rules":null,"editableRegion":null,"recentUserActions":null,"chatSectionId":"1"},"id":"1bb131dc-4ab6-447a-8d1c-e1d3d2ba998b","agentMetadata":{"coderAgent":{"kind":""},"model":""}},{"traceId":"3ecf7deaf3d8dd4d","entity":"SYSTEM","markdownText":"\u003e Gemini 2.5 generated this response due to high traffic on Gemini 3\n\nThat's an excellent and crucial question! Storing secrets securely is one of the most important parts of deploying an application.\n\nYou should **never** put your `JWT_SECRET` directly into the `render.yaml` file. Because `render.yaml` is committed to your source control (like GitHub), adding a secret to it would expose it to anyone who has access to your repository.\n\nThe correct way to handle this is to use Render's built-in secret management. You can configure your `render.yaml` to expect an environment variable, but you will set the actual secret value in the Render dashboard.\n\n### 1. Update Your `render.yaml`\n\nModify your `render.yaml` to tell Render that the `JWT_SECRET` will be provided through the dashboard. You do this by adding the key and setting `sync: false`. This prevents Render from overwriting the value you set in the UI on subsequent deploys.\n\n```diff\n--- a/home/perrymckay1/render.yaml\n+++ b/home/perrymckay1/render.yaml\n@@ -23,7 +23,9 @@\n         fromService:\n           type: redis\n           name: food-truck-redis\n           property: connectionString\n-      # IMPORTANT: Add other secrets like SECRET_KEY in the Render dashboard.\n+      # IMPORTANT: Secrets like JWT_SECRET are added in the Render dashboard.\n+      - key: JWT_SECRET\n+        sync: false # This value is managed in the Render dashboard\n \n   # -----------------\n   # Redis Cache\n\n```\n\n### 2. Add the Secret in the Render Dashboard\n\nAfter you commit and push this change, your Blueprint will be updated. Now, you need to provide the actual secret value securely.\n\n1.  Go to your **Render Dashboard**.\n2.  Navigate to your `food-truck-app` service.\n3.  Click on the **Environment** tab in the service's navigation.\n4.  Under \"Environment Variables\", click **\"Add Environment Variable\"**.\n5.  Enter `JWT_SECRET` for the **Key** and paste your actual secret string into the **Value** field.\n6.  Click **\"Save Changes\"**.\n\nRender encrypts and stores this value securely. Your application will automatically restart with the new environment variable available as `process.env.JWT_SECRET`, without the secret ever touching your code repository.\n\n\u003c!--\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]How do I generate a strong, secure JWT_SECRET?[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]How do I use these environment variables in my Node.js code?[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n--\u003e","chatSectionId":"1","promptCitations":[{"startIndex":1046,"endIndex":1228,"filepath":"/home/perrymckay1/render.yaml","citationText":"fromService:\n           type: redis\n           name: food-truck-redis\n           property: connectionString\n-      # IMPORTANT: Add other secrets like SECRET_KEY in the Render dashbo"}],"ideContext":{"currentFile":{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/render.yaml","language":"yaml","selection":{"start":828,"end":828},"includedReason":"CURRENTLY_OPEN"},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":[{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","language":"dockerfile","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CHAT_FILE_REFERENCED"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/cors/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/@types/node/diagnostics_channel.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home